[EncDescription_data/units/tanks/pol/renault_r35_pol]
Poles bought 100 Renault R-35 tanks in France in April 1939. First transport with 49 tanks on board arrived to Poland by sea in July and these tanks were given to 12th tank battalion based in Lutsk. During first days of war several companies of this battalion formed 21st light tank battalion led by major Ezhi Lucki. In the middle of September this battalion was ordered to support colonel Stanislav Maczek's 10th cavalry brigade which fought to the north of Lvov. Unfortunately, 45 R-35 tanks, eagerly awaited by Maczek, failed to reach the brigade. On 18th September 34 of these tanks led by major Lucki himself crossed Polish-Romanian border. Remaining tanks, led by leitenant Josef Jakubowicz, arrived to Lvov on 17th September and joined the "Dubno" group. This tank detachment fought against Wermacht near Kamenka-Strumilovo and against Red Army near Krasnoje and lost all of it's tanks before 25th September.

[EncDescription_data/units/tanks/pol/hotchkis_h35_pol]
Four Hotchkiss H-35 tanks arrived into Poland in 1938. During September campaign they were in leitenant Yakubovsky detachment and were lost while fighting in the "Dubno" group.

